<br>
NEEDS!!!<br>
1) You need a master pottery skill, preferably at least level 130.<br>
2) You need to do a little farming in Crystal Caverns.<br>
3) You need decent faction with Thurgadin.<br>
<br>
GETTING A MASTER POTTERY SKILL is cake, but for most melees it's just time consuming.<br>
<br>
I HIGHLY recommend doing your pottery at the Thurgadin bank cause all the stuff you need is there. But if someone else is using the pottery wheel, it can get frustrating.<br>
<br>
With most trade skills ya wanna sell the results back to the vendor to recoup on expenses. You would have to fire the pottery in the kiln to sell it back to the vendor and firing is trivial at like level 20. It just aint worth it. Destroy the stuff you make, it's cheap enough.<br>
<br>
Make small Bowls until level 102<br>
1) Small Block of Clay<br>
2) Bowl Sketch<br>
3) a water flask<br>
*** combine in the pottery wheel and if successful destroy your pretty creation.<br>
<br>
Make medium bowls until level 122<br>
1) Block of clay<br>
2) Medium Bowl Sketch<br>
3) a water flask<br>
*** combine in the pottery wheel and cram result into the round file.<br>
<br>
Make Large bowls until level 130 (or max to 14<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
1) Large Block of Clay<br>
2) Large Bowl Sketch<br>
3) Glass Shard<br>
4) a water flask<br>
*** combine in pottery wheel and see if results will stick to the ceiling.<br>
<br>
NOW THAT YOUR LEET POTTERY SKILLZ ARE UP, Lets go farming.<br>
<br>
Goto Crystal Caverns and Kill, Kill, Kill. Mostly Kill the Rygor Miners to get small bricks of velium and Small pieces of Velium. Loot other stuff off the mobs if you want, by it's super heavy and you could get tired of running to town to sell it. Also find the Crystalline Spiders and kill them repeatedly to collect Crystaline Silks.<br>
<br>
NOW THAT YOUR HAVE FULFILLED YOUR GROCERY LIST...<br>
<br>
Lets go back to thurgadin bank and make a Gate Potion.<br>
<br>
1) Combine a small brick of Velium, three unstacked crystalline silks and two glass shards in a pottery wheel. You will get back an unfired velium vial, if you're LUCKY.<br>
<br>
2) Combine the unfired velium vial and a HQ firing sheet in the kiln and receive a velium vial. Again, luck be with you.<br>
<br>
3) Run down to Frundle Frenklar which is west of the bank. Say to her &quot;What velium vapors?&quot; and she'll toss a velium purifier at you.<br>
<br>
4) Insert into the Velium Purifier your velium vial and 2 small pieces of velium. Then click on combine, WHAM!! you've got a gate potion.<br>
<br>
Sure, it's got a 10 second cast time.<br>
Sure, it takes you back to thurgadin and not your bind spot.<br>
But isn't that better than being stuck at the bottom of a long long dungeon? I would label this quest a &quot;MUST DO&quot; for all non-gating peoples.<br>
<br>
Had to share....<br>
<br>
Rhiat, 49 Rogue<br>
Keveok, 60 High Priest<br>
